### Schema Context

**routine_mappings table** (`/Users/ryanr/Code/hevy-planner/migrations/0001_initial.sql`, lines 39-44):
```sql
CREATE TABLE routine_mappings (
  user_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
  program_routine_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  hevy_routine_id TEXT NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (user_id, program_routine_id)
);
```

Composite primary key on `(user_id, program_routine_id)`, ensuring at most one mapping per program routine per user. This is the only way to detect existing Hevy routines on re-setup.

