const deepLink = `https://hevy.com/routine/${created.id}`;
return sseResponse(
  executeScript(`window.open('${deepLink}', '_blank')`)
);
```

#### Step 8: Add cleanup route and handler

**File: `/Users/ryanr/Code/hevy-planner/src/index.ts`**

Add a new route: `POST /api/cleanup-routines`

```typescript
const cleanupMatch = path === "/api/cleanup-routines";
if (method === "POST" && cleanupMatch) {
  return await handleCleanupRoutines(env, auth.userId);
}
```

The handler:
```typescript
async function handleCleanupRoutines(env: Env, userId: string): Promise<Response> {
  const user = await getUser(env.DB, userId);
  if (!user || !user.hevy_api_key) {
    return sseResponse(patchElements(`<div class="card"><p>Connect your Hevy API key first.</p></div>`, { selector: "#content", mode: "prepend" }));
  }

  const program = await loadProgram(env.DB, userId);
  const client = new HevyClient(user.hevy_api_key);
  const allHevyRoutines = await client.getAllRoutines();

  // Build set of known routine titles from program
  const knownTitles = new Set(program.routines.map(r => r.title));

  // Find duplicates: routines with same title in same folder
  const byTitleAndFolder = new Map<string, typeof allHevyRoutines>();
  for (const r of allHevyRoutines) {
    const key = `${r.title}::${r.folderId}`;
    const list = byTitleAndFolder.get(key) ?? [];
    list.push(r);
    byTitleAndFolder.set(key, list);
  }

  const toDelete: string[] = [];
  for (const [, routines] of byTitleAndFolder) {
    if (routines.length > 1) {
      // Keep the most recently updated, delete the rest
      routines.sort((a, b) => /* by updatedAt desc */);
      toDelete.push(...routines.slice(1).map(r => r.id));
    }
  }

  let deleted = 0;
  let failed = 0;
  for (const id of toDelete) {
    try {
      await client.deleteRoutine(id);
      deleted++;
    } catch {
      failed++;
    }
  }

  return sseResponse(
    patchElements(
      `<div class="card"><p style="color:var(--green)">Cleanup complete: ${deleted} duplicate(s) removed, ${failed} failed.</p></div>`,
      { selector: "#content", mode: "prepend" }
    )
  );
}
```

If `deleteRoutine` turns out not to work (Hevy API may not support it), degrade to reporting which duplicates exist and their IDs, so the user can delete them manually in the Hevy app.

#### Step 9: Add `updatedAt` to `HevyRoutine` interface

**File: `/Users/ryanr/Code/hevy-planner/src/hevy/client.ts`**

The live API returns `createdAt` and `updatedAt` on routines. Add these to the interface so the cleanup logic can sort by them:
```typescript
export interface HevyRoutine {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  folderId?: number;
  createdAt?: string;
  updatedAt?: string;
  exercises: HevyRoutineExercise[];
}
```

#### Step 10: Write tests for new pure domain functions

**File: `/Users/ryanr/Code/hevy-planner/test/domain/hevy-sync.test.ts`**

Add test cases for:
- `computeFolderAssignments`: verifies folderGroup takes priority, isDaily defaults to "Daily", others default to program title.
- `reconcileRoutines`: verifies (a) existing D1 mapping -> update, (b) title match in folder -> update, (c) no match -> create.

Follow the existing test patterns (vitest, import from `../../src/domain/hevy-sync`).

---

### Sequencing Summary

| Phase | Step | Files Modified | Risk |
|-------|------|----------------|------|
| 1 | Schema + types | `program.schema.json`, `types.ts`, program JSON | Low -- additive |
| 2 | HevyClient methods | `hevy/client.ts` | Low -- new methods only |
| 3 | Domain logic | `domain/hevy-sync.ts` | Low -- pure functions, testable |
| 4 | Migration | new `0004_routine_folder_id.sql`, `types.ts`, `queries.ts` | Low -- additive ALTER TABLE |
| 5 | Setup rewrite | `index.ts` handleSetup | Medium -- core flow change |
| 6 | Deep links | `fragments/today.ts`, `index.ts` handleTodaySSE | Low -- UI change |
| 7 | Push handler | `index.ts` handlePush | Low |
| 8 | Cleanup route | `index.ts` new handler | Medium -- DELETE endpoint uncertain |
| 9 | HevyRoutine fields | `hevy/client.ts` | Low -- additive |
| 10 | Tests | `test/domain/hevy-sync.test.ts` | Low |

### Open Questions / Risks

1. **DELETE endpoint uncertainty**: The Hevy MCP tools do not expose `deleteRoutine`. The REST API likely supports `DELETE /v1/routines/{id}` but this must be verified with a live test (`curl -X DELETE -H "api-key: ..." https://api.hevyapp.com/v1/routines/{id}`). If it does not exist, the cleanup handler should report duplicates without deleting.

2. **Rate limiting**: `getAllRoutines()` paginates at max 10 per page. For a user with 60+ routines, that is 6+ sequential API calls. Combined with folder creation and routine create/update, setup could make 20+ API calls. The existing `request()` method already throws on 429. Consider adding a simple delay between calls (e.g. 200ms) or exponential backoff retry on 429.

3. **Deep link URL format**: `https://hevy.com/routine/{id}` is the assumed format. Must verify this opens the routine in the Hevy app (via universal links on iOS) or at minimum in the Hevy web view. An alternative is the `hevy://` custom URL scheme if the web URL does not work.

4. **Folder naming strategy**: The plan uses `folderGroup` from the program JSON. If the user has not set `folderGroup` in their program JSON, the fallback grouping (Daily / program title) should be acceptable. The alternative of deriving groups from routine `sortOrder` or `subtitle` patterns (e.g. "Session A/B/C/D" -> "Main Sessions") is fragile.

### Critical Files for Implementation

- `/Users/ryanr/Code/hevy-planner/src/hevy/client.ts` - Add `getAllRoutines()`, `deleteRoutine()`, update `HevyRoutine` interface with `folderId`/timestamps
- `/Users/ryanr/Code/hevy-planner/src/domain/hevy-sync.ts` - Add `computeFolderAssignments()` and `reconcileRoutines()` pure domain functions
- `/Users/ryanr/Code/hevy-planner/src/index.ts` - Rewrite `handleSetup` routine sync (lines 560-601), update `handlePush` deep link, add `handleCleanupRoutines`
- `/Users/ryanr/Code/hevy-planner/src/fragments/today.ts` - Update `carsCard` and `heroRoutineCard` to render deep links when `hevy_routine_id` is available
- `/Users/ryanr/Code/hevy-planner/src/types.ts` - Add `folderGroup` to `Routine`, add `hevy_folder_id` to `RoutineMappingRow`

